Ready for your next tropical adventure? 🌴☀️🌊 This is your sign! Consider escaping to the enchanting ANTIGUA AND BARBUDA for your next paradise getaway! 

PS - Let’s talk about the view from my balcony at The Pineapple Beach Club! Waking up to this every morning for a week, was everything ! 

✈️ @delta 
📍 @pineapplebeachclub - is a fantastic all-inclusive resort that caters exclusively to adults. Situated on a beautiful beachfront location, this resort offers a picturesque environment that is perfect for relaxation and fun. This beautiful resort offers wide range of amenities. Pineapple Beach Club also features multiple swimming pools, like the infinity pool that’s right on the beach. In addition to many amenities, Pineapple Beach Club is also known for its amazing friendly service. Overall, if you're looking for a great all inclusive resort, Pineapple Beach Club is an excellent choice.

Work, Play, Slay! 💼✨ Grateful for the chance to co-judge the Barbizon’s ( @barbizonmodel ) Regional Acting/Modeling Competition in Dallas last week. Special THANK YOU SHOUTOUT to my amazing agent ( @blackroseagency ) and boss queen @anissashantele for always believing in me and opening doors to opportunities like this! It was a privilege to be invited / join Black Rose Agency, to judge and discover new talent along side / with Anissa. Someone who I appreciate, highly respect and one of my real life inspirations. #familyforever 🙌🌟Such a blessed & fun weekend overall!
This was a “full circle” weekend for me, because I was a participant in one of these competitions when I was 12. I still remember it like it was yesterday. So being invited to judge and meeting these kids, teens and young adults ( That we selected ) at the callbacks was pretty personal for me.
I definitely saw some great and *Future Star* quality talent! 💫💫💫

#FunFact: The color “Chartreuse” 🎨☘️🍐🥝 was inspired by a famous French liqueur called Chartreuse. The liqueur was named after the Chartreuse Mountains in eastern France, where the Carthusian monks first produced it in the 18th century. The liqueur is known for its distinct green yellow color, which became associated with the bold shade we now know as Chartreuse. 

Cheers to life’s vibrant moments! 💚
